This paper discusses interpretability and trust in machine learning systems, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of humans in understanding and trusting machine learning decisions, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential biases that can arise when humans rely too heavily on machine learning predictions, which is a topic that falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
